The AnalysisEngineExample testcase in the Monitoring.UI.Examples.ISV testsuite fails as a result of this defect.
Alex, please have a look at this problem.  It may be a candidate for i4.
This is a regression introduced in 168562. Assigning to the owner of 168562 to fix this regression.

Created an attachment (id=67265)
Patch

Code was assuming that all CBE events had extended data. This is not true for the data imported in the example.

Fix checks to see if there are any extended data elements, and then sets the message appropriately
Candidate for i4 as it is a regression.
Can you please attach a test case to test this fix.
Actually there is already a test case available, just make sure it explicity checks for errors when viewing log record properties for the sample log.

Patch checked in as per PMc approval. Please mark the defect as being fixed.
As an additional comment, it would have been cleaner to include the checking for extended data elements inside the setMessage method so that this method contains the whole decision logic, but that's OK for now.
The patch was committed to CVS.  Resolving this bugzilla as FIXED.
